post_text:
TxConnect Parent Portal moves to Ascender Parent Portal!!!!!!
The Woodville I.S.D. Ascender Parent Portal will be available for parent access and use beginning July 27th. Parents/guardians of RETURNING Woodville ISD students will receive a letter in the mail that contains their student's Portal ID. After receiving the letter parents of RETURNING students can use the link to access the Ascender site. It will be necessary for all "new" parent portal users to set up a new account by clicking on the "New User" link and following the registration instructions. If you already have a Parent Portal account, it is NOT necessary to create an account, your information remained the same from last year. If you have trouble opening your current account, you will need to verify your email for contacts at your child's campus. Your email address must be the same entered on your child's registration information.
Due to changes in registration procedures, all students must pre-register for the 2020-2021 school year. Registration deadline is August 7.

post_text: Woodville I.S.D. mourns the loss of a dear friend and colleague, Reggie Williams. A long-time educator and coach, Reggie was an integral part of our school family whom we all loved and respected. Services will be held on Wednesday, October 2nd at noon at the Eagle Summit Auditorium. Out of respect for Reggie and his family and to ensure all students and staff are able to attend and pay their last respects, Woodville I.S.D. will not have school on Wednesday, October 2, 2019. He will be greatly missed and our heartfelt thoughts and prayers continue to go out to his family and friends. Please see the attached document for complete details.

post_text: Today we mourn the loss of a dear friend and colleague, Reginald "Reggie" Williams. A long-time educator and coach, Reggie was an integral part of our school family whom we all loved and respected. He served as a model of faith, strength, and perseverance and is leaving behind a positive, lasting legacy that will continue to impact the lives of many. He will be greatly missed. Our heartfelt thoughts and prayers go out to Reggie's family and friends. Services are pending with Coleman's Family Mortuary.

post_text:
As part of the Beaumont Foundation’s ongoing commitment to supporting education, the Wayne A. Reaud Excellence in Education Award was created to celebrate and recognize superior contributions of teachers whose leadership and dedication inspire a spirit of learning in students of all backgrounds and abilities. Fifteen teachers are selected annually to receive this prestigious Award in recognition of their outstanding contributions to the education system of Southeast Texas.

Our own Mrs. Amee Scarberry (7th grade writing teacher at WMS) has been chosen as one of this years recipients. A well deserved honor as Mrs. Scarberry fits the above criteria perfectly.

Congratulations Mrs. Scarberry! We are super proud to call you ours!
